{"session_id": "83ea8135-ac8d-44d1-b34a-a01c542cd4b1", "task": "Implement the following plan:\n\n# Plan: Render Markdown in Prompt Section\n\n## Context\nThe Prompt section in checkpoint detail's Overview tab displays raw markdown text. The Context and Plan sections already use `renderMarkdown()` (glamour-based), but the Prompt section uses plain `wordWrap()`. When a prompt contains markdown (headers, code blocks, lists, etc.), it shows as unformatted text.\n\n## Change\n\n### `pkg/ui/dashboard/checkpoint_detail.go` \u2014 line 89\n\nReplace `wordWrap` with `renderMarkdown` for the Prompt content:\n\n```go\n// Before (line 89):\npromptBox := panelStyle.Width(contentWidth).Render(wordWrap(cp.Prompt, contentWidth-4))\n\n// After:\nrendered := renderMarkdown(cp.Prompt, contentWidth-4)\npromptBox := panelStyle.Width(contentWidth).Render(rendered)\n```\n\nThis matches how Context (line 99) and Plan (lines 115, 237) already render their content.\n\n## Files Modified\n- `pkg/ui/dashboard/checkpoint_detail.go` \u2014 one line change (line 89)\n\n## Verification\n- `make build`\n- Visual: prompt content with markdown (headers, code blocks, lists) renders with formatting instead of raw text\n\n\nIf you need specific details from before exiting plan mode (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /Users/arvos/.claude/projects/-Users-arvos-Tactic-workspaces-workspace-entire-local-cli-entire-local/67920851-1aa5-4602-91b5-bc6bc1ad4386.jsonl", "stage": "apply", "user_decision": "approve", "edit_distance": 0.6666666666666667, "user_feedback_text": "", "change_type": "go", "turn_number": 2, "_swechat_pushback": "non_pushback", "_swechat_persona": "expert_nitpicker", "_swechat_mode": "collaborative", "_swechat_intent": "create new code", "_swechat_success": "28.0", "_swechat_agent_pct": 33.33333333333333}
